# Critvue Project Context

You are working on **Critvue**, a hybrid AI-human feedback platform for creators to receive structured, high-quality critiques on their work.

## Required Reading

Before starting any work on this project, you must read and understand the following documentation files:

1. **Product Brief**: `/home/user/Critvue/docs/product/critvue_product_brief.md`
   - Product vision, target users, problems being solved
   - Key features and business model
   - Expansion potential

2. **Tech Stack**: `/home/user/Critvue/docs/technical/critvue_techstack.md`
   - Frontend: Next.js 14, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, Framer Motion
   - Backend: FastAPI, PostgreSQL, Supabase/Railway
   - AI: OpenAI GPT-4-Turbo, Claude 2.1/3
   - Auth, payments, hosting, and infrastructure details

3. **Brand & Design System**: `/home/user/Critvue/docs/product/critvue_brand_style.md`
   - Design philosophy (Apple-like minimalism with creative warmth)
   - Color palette, typography, UI elements
   - Motion and interaction patterns

4. **Mobile-First UX Guide**: `/home/user/Critvue/docs/product/mobile_guide.md`
   - Mobile design philosophy and layout principles
   - Key screens and user flows
   - Interaction patterns and accessibility requirements

## Documentation Structure

All documentation is organized in `/home/user/Critvue/docs/`:
- **docs/product/** - Product vision, brand, and design guidelines
- **docs/technical/** - Technical architecture and implementation plans
- **docs/frontend/** - Frontend-specific documentation
- **backend/docs/** - Backend-specific documentation

See `/home/user/Critvue/docs/README.md` for the complete documentation index.

## Project Principles

- **Mobile-first**: Prioritize mobile experience, desktop polish follows
- **Minimalist design**: Apple-like elegance with creative flourishes
- **Modular architecture**: Separate AI logic from human review logic
- **Performance**: <2s time-to-interactive on mobile
- **Accessibility**: High contrast, resizable text, VoiceOver tested

## Key Technical Decisions

- Use Next.js App Router for frontend routing
- Tailwind CSS with 4pt/8pt spacing scale
- Async operations for AI reviews and notifications
- Stripe for subscriptions and reviewer payouts
- Structured AI prompts with category-specific templates

When working on this project, always refer to these documents to ensure consistency with the product vision, design system, and technical architecture.
